When we normalize the stalking of celebrities, we feed this notion that stalking is a compliment; a sign that you are worthy of obsession. 

First, we're met with skepticism : "Are you sure this is really happening?"

Then we're told "Wow, you should be flattered!" 

If stalking is something that happens to beautiful famous people then clearly, you should take your stalker as proof that you are beautiful and adored, too. 

And if you're not what society views as desirable? Then you're met with outright denial because why would anyone be obsessed with someone like you?! 

It's a game we all lose. 

It's Stalking Awareness Month #NSAM2023 Let's be mindful of the ways we talk about stalking and start making the connections. 

Full PSA available at OutsideOfTheShadows.ca 
Words by me (@yellowmanteau)

Sometimes I worry that I spend too much time worrying so I try to stop worrying by reading books about how to stop worrying or books about people who worry too much and then I find new things to worry about and sometimes I’m like, well at least I can make art about it but then other times I worry that people are tired of seeing art about worrying. So sometimes I make drawings like this one and don’t post it for like 8 months because I worry no one will like it, then I remember that because of the algorithm no one will see it anyway so maybe it’s fine? 🤷🏻‍♀️

social_posts.post_text: I’m teaching an experimental animation class at @countyarts from May 23 to June 20. During this 5-week class students will learn the basics of animation and explore different techniques such as frame by frame, paper cutout and claymation stop-motion animation. All of the techniques will be presented using affordable and DIY methods accessible to all artistic levels. No fancy equipment or previous animation experience is required. Sign up at The County Arts. Thank you!!

Feelings! Feelings! Feelings! And More! at @carbonlifepec 
July 6 to 23, 2023
Artist reception July 6 from 6-8. Mark your calendars!!! 

Have you ever wondered how many feelings can fit into a single person at once? Feelings! Feelings! Feelings! And More! is a celebration and a lamentation of emotional excess. It is a collection of drawings, paintings, moving images, ephemeral emotions and rambling thoughts held together with long faces and soft hues. In a world that rewards careful coolness, dare to be a bit of a mess.

A behind the scenes look at the making of my art exhibition: Feelings! Feelings! Feelings! And More! At @carbonlifepec in Picton, Ontario from July 6-23.

When the moon is in cancer ♋️ 

I want to feel the feelings
I keep under my feelings 
Below my sarcasm 
Beneath my anger 
Held down 
With humour 
Blunted in pastels

I take my feelings 
And pull them apart: 
A piece for now 
A piece before sleep 
A piece to share 
A piece to keep

I wish I could feel things sparsely 
Instead of everything at once 
Or nothing at all
Super Blue Moon Feelings 🌝

I don’t want to capitalize 
On all my woes 
Sometimes disappointment 
Needs to 
Run its course
Without ever revealing
A bright side 

(She says as she makes art
Out of her sadness 
Again)

🚨💡NEW ARTIST SPOTLIGHT: AMBIVALENTLY YOURS 🌷

Introducing the soft and powerful work of Ambivalently Yours! In the works of the semi-anonymous, perpetually ambivalent artist Ambivalently Yours, every hue carries a depth of emotion wrapped in vulnerability. The portraits, and tender micro poems that accompany them, often dance on the line between melancholy and might while hinting at the value our most tender feelings can hold. 

From collaborative beginnings on Tumblr to a mighty instagram presence, Ambivalently Yours’ world of soft yet powerful imagery is a wonder to behold. There is something healing and soothing about seeing vulnerability and emotionality as a symbol of strength, a testament to the complex beauty of the human spirit. It’s equally fascinating to dive into the intricacies of being an artist. 

Take some time to read about how Ambivalently Yours blends colours and emotions with insightful writing and how her imaginative style evolved! Article link is in our bio 🌸
